@stoneisland Sound has released an exclusive special edition vinyl of Sir Render, the latest album from Navy Blue, the musical project of our cover star @sageelsesser. Originally released in June, the record is one of Elsesser's most introspective works, exploring spiritual inquiry, grief, resilience and personal transformation through the recurring metaphor of a knight confronting his inner conflict.⁠
⁠
Featuring Earl Sweatshirt, Armand Hammer, Mike Shabb and the late Ka, with production from The Alchemist, Jason Wool, Shungu and Sage himself, Sir Render also includes narration by James Earl Jones. The Stone Island Sound edition brings the project into a physical format, extending its vision beyond music into a collectible object.

